tools/server/llama_dflash_bridge.{h,cpp}:
  NEW. Implements dflash27b::DFlashTarget interface against llama_context.

  Working methods:
    - verify_batch     → llama_decode + per-position argmax
    - snapshot_kv      → llama_memory_seq_cp(live → snapshot)
    - restore_kv       → seq_rm(live) + seq_cp(snapshot → live)
    - is_eos           → llama_vocab_is_eog
    - hidden_size      → llama_model_n_embd
    - mask_token_id    → llama_vocab_pad (Qwen3.5/3.6 PAD sentinel)
    - capture_layer_ids → 4 evenly-spread trunk layers (hardcoded for v0)

  Stubbed (TODO Phase 0h v1):
    - embed_tokens     → zero-fill (no public llama.h access to tok_embd)
    - project_hidden_to_tokens → token 0 (no public lm_head access)
    - Real feature capture during target forward — requires either
      custom layer hook in llama_decode OR parallel ggml graph.

  With stubs in place dflash drafter acceptance will be near-chance; v0
  ships with --decode-engine legacy default. v1 wires real capture + lm_head
  access for production-grade dflash decode.

tools/server/CMakeLists.txt:
  Conditionally include bridge sources when LLAMA_DFLASH=ON. Bridge compiles
  alongside server.cpp; LLAMA_HAS_DFLASH define controls activation.

